name: Horimon 006 麒麟;QILIN
description:
Meaning : Smartness, Loyal, Protection, Peace, Lucky

Qilin is a legendary creature that appears in Chinese mythology. Qilin is a symbol of peace and it appears when the next great king who will bring peace to the country is born. Qilin's head looks like a dragon, it's legs like a horse, it's tail like a cow and has scales. It's about 5m long however it's a very calm and peaceful creature and never kills any insects or flowers even when it walks.
